<plot>Kilian is a cameraman who lives in London. His life is ordered and well organized. A anonymous videotape arrives in the mail containing crowd footage in a train station during peak hours. He finds himself amongst the crowd. The daily arrival of more tapes grows his obsession with cameras, pictured through a dreamlike sequence in Venice. However, it is Venice that is the arrival point of Kilian's psychological journey, which reveals a new perspective of what we have so far believed to be true</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?214371</url></doc>
